message.content:
A caterpillar is a larval form of a butterfly or moth.
They are typically cylindrical in shape and have multiple segments.
Their body is often covered in small bristles or hairs.
Caterpillars vary in color, ranging from green, brown, yellow, and even black.
They have three pairs of legs on their thoracic segments and multiple pairs of prolegs on their abdomen.
Caterpillars can often be found in gardens, fields, and forests.
They are herbivores and eat the leaves of plants to fuel their growth and development.
